An investigation by Shu et al. [
 11] using an aroma extract dilution analysis (AEDA) of the aroma concentrate of soy milk made from a major Japanese soybean cultivar, Fukuyutaka (FK), revealed 20 key aroma compounds having flavor dilution (FD) factors of not less than 64. Among them; 2-isopropyl-3-methoxypyrazine; 
 cis-4,5-epoxy-(E)-2-decenal; 
 trans-4,5-epoxy-(E)-2-decenal; 3-hydroxy-4,5-dimethyl-2(5H)-furanone; and 2â€²-aminoacetophenone were identified as the key aroma compounds in soy milk for the first time. Generally, it is believed that aroma compounds might be generated from lipids, amino acids, sugars, and ferulic acid present in food.
